e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the earlier decision</a> describes i=
t:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">LATIII, a Delaware trust cre=
ated in 2005, operated the Life Accumulation Program (the =E2=80=9CProgram=
=E2=80=9D) which invited certain =E2=80=9Cqualified=E2=80=9D senior citizen=
s to create Delaware statutory trusts which would then be utilized to acqui=
re life insurance policies on their behalf.=C2=A0LATIII provided all of the=
 capital to the trusts to pay for the premiums on the policies.=C2=A0In add=
ition, LATIII was made the initial =E2=80=9Csole beneficiary=E2=80=9D of th=
e trust, with power to transfer the policies to other secondary market purc=
hasers.=C2=A0The senior citizens who participated in the Program received 3=
% of the face value of the life insurance policies taken out by LATIII via =
the Delaware statutory trusts.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>Apparently Barotz did this a lot: She had multiple life insurance policies=
