<span>[9]</span>
</a> She got the $150,000, the investor made the premium payments, and she =
signed a disclosure statement acknowledging=C2=A0that =E2=80=9Ca third part=
y investor with an =E2=80=98economic interest=E2=80=99=C2=A0in the death of=
 Ms. Barotz could own any life insurance policies procured on Ms. Barotz's =
life through the Program.=E2=80=9D That=C2=A0<em>sort of=C2=A0</em>says =E2=
=80=9Cwe have an economic incentive to murder you=E2=80=9D? Again, though: =
no murder!</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2011, Life Accumulation Trust=
 III sold the policy to Financial Credit Investment, an Apollo entity. From=
 the complaint:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">William Sulliva=
n, an Apollo employee who served as the managing director of the FCI suite =
of funds between 2010 and at least 2019, indicated in trial testimony that =
=E2=80=9CFCI is mainly focused on longevity mortality risk assets,=E2=80=9D=
 which are=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cmost sensitive to the risk of people living longer=
 or not . . . by buying life insurance policies that people no longer need =
anymore and would otherwise surrender back to the carrier.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=
=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Because =E2=80=9CFCI has a lot of capit=
al put to work,=E2=80=9D the suite of funds does not dabble in the individu=
al policy market but, instead, =E2=80=9Conly purchase[s] portfolios of poli=
cies from existing investors ...=C2=A0that have already aggregated a portfo=
lio,=E2=80=9D otherwise referred to as the =E2=80=9Ctertiary market.=E2=80=
=9D=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So Apollo allegedly =
bought life insurance policies in bulk, without necessarily knowing which w=
ere (1) legal valid normal life insurance policies whose holders eventually=
 decided to sell them or (2) bad fake policies like this one. But then Baro=
tz died, the policy paid out, the Apollo fund claimed the benefit, and Baro=
tz=E2=80=99s estate sued for the money back, arguing that this was a bad fa=
ke insurance policy.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-10" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; ba=
