</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The basic idea of a <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35212621.286353/aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtp=
cGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvRGVsdGFfb25l/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB851cae6e" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
>delta one desk</a> is that you are selling Thing X to a customer, and buyi=
ng Thing Y from the market, and Thing X and Thing Y are exactly equivalent.=
 Thus =E2=80=9Cdelta one=E2=80=9D: If you sell stock options, you hedge the=
 options by trading stock, and the amount of stock you need to buy or sell =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0the =E2=80=9Cdelta=E2=80=9D of the option =E2=80=94=C2=A0cha=
nges over time as the stock price changes. But if you sell index futures co=
ntracts, you can hedge them by buying the stocks in the index (or an exchan=
ge-traded fund, etc.), and the ratio never changes: It=E2=80=99s always one=
-for-one, always a delta of one. You=E2=80=99re buying a thing at a low pri=
ce and selling an equivalent thing at, ideally, a higher price.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At some level this should be a fairly low-risk busines=
s: The stuff that you are long and the stuff that you are short exactly off=
set each other, so you shouldn=E2=80=99t make or lose money as the market m=
oves. On the other hand, you are trying to make money, and the only way to =
make money is to take <em>some </em>risk.=C2=A0If you are not taking market=
 risk =E2=80=94=C2=A0if all your trades are fully hedged =E2=80=94=C2=A0and=
 you=E2=80=99re making money, then you=E2=80=99re taking some other, slight=
ly more esoteric risk. You=E2=80=99re taking funding risk, or interest-rate=
 risk. You=E2=80=99re taking the risk of the basis between Thing X and almo=
st-but-not-quite-identical Thing Y. You=E2=80=99re writing one-day lookback=
s into your swaps trades, and taking the legal and reputational risk that a=
 regulator will <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35=
212621.286353/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwM=
